{"lemma":"شِهاب","slug":"شِهاب","root":"ش.ه.ب","root_slug":"ش-ه-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ه-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شِهاب","root":"شهب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23179","n23180"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%90%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%A8"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brand, blaze, burning flame","examples":[{"text":"إِلَّا مَنِ ٱسْتَرَقَ ٱلسَّمْعَ فَأَتْبَعَهُ شِهَابٌ مُّبِينٌ","english":"Except one who steals a hearing and is pursued by a clear burning flame."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brand, a feeling of inflammation or irritation on the body","examples":[{"text":"الصاب هو العلقم، وقال أبو حنيفة: الصاب شجر إذا اعتصر خرج منه كهيئة اللبن، فربّما نزتْ منه نزية، أي قطرة، فتقع في العين فكأنّها شهاب نار، وربّما أضعفت البصر.","english":"Aṣ-ṣāb is the squirting cucumber. Abū Ḥanīfa said: Aṣ-ṣāb is a shrub from which one brings out a milkish sap on squeeze. If a squirt, that is to say a single drop of it, touches the eye, it is afterwards [hurting] like fire-brand. It potentially weakens the eyesight."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"meteor"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a surname"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃi.haːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23179","headword_ar":"شَهَابٌ","root":"$hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhaAbapN","text_ar":"شُهَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, Kr, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk mixed with much water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mixture of which one third is milk and the rest water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) Az heard several of the Arabs apply the former term to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk mixed with water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called on account of the alteration of its colour. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n23180","headword_ar":"شِهَابٌ","root":"$hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", in its primary acceptation,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEolap","text_ar":"شُعْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brand"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flame"},{"kind":"text","text":"(app. the former, agreeably"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1609},{"kind":"text","text":"with what follows,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEolap","text_ar":"شُعْلَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fire gleaming"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"radiating:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) accord. to ISk,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a firebrand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stick in which is fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to AHeyth, originally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick, in which is fire gleaming"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"radiating:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhubN","text_ar":"شُهُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and some allow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhobN","text_ar":"شُهْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhobaAnN","text_ar":"شُهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ihobaAnN","text_ar":"شِهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is strange, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohubN","text_ar":"اَشْهُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last is [a pl. of pauc., but] thought by IM to be a quasi-pl. n. (TA.) The reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$ihaAbi qabasK","text_ar":"بِشِهَابِ قَبَسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$ihaAbK qabasK","text_ar":"بِشِهَابٍ قَبَسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxvii. 7], is an instance of a word prefixed to another identical therewith. (Fr. L.) ―         -b2-  Hence, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shooting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling, star;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like of a star, that darts down"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is hurled"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after a devil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as occurring in the Kur [xv. 18 and] xxxvii. 10; and in a trad.; respecting the attempt of a devil to hear, by stealth, words uttered in heaven. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uhubu","text_ar":"الشُّهُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The shining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brightly-shining, stars:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seven stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"planets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, not the Pleiades (which are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ajomu","text_ar":"النَّجْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Moon, Mercury, Venus, the Sun, Mars, Jupiter, and Saturn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the first three of which are said by Freytag to be called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SigaAru Al$~uhubi","text_ar":"صِغَارُ الشُّهُبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  For another meaning assigned in the K to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uhubu","text_ar":"الشُّهُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uhobu","text_ar":"الشُّهْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohabu","text_ar":"اَشْهَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ihaAbN","text_ar":"شِهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who is penetrating, sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"energetic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an affair; (K, TA;) as being likened to the [shooting] star. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a fulaAnFA la$ihaAbu","text_ar":"اـِنَّ فُلَانًا لَشِهَابُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobK","text_ar":"حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily such a man is one who is penetrating, sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"energetic, in war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i $uhobaAnu Aljayo$i","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ شُهْبَانُ الجَيْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are the braves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heroes, of the army"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b6-  Also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain devil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in a trad.: hence the Prophet changed the name of a certain man [originally] thus named. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","Az","Akh"]}]}}